article.headline: High Point 58, Radford 57
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Danny Gathings made two free throws with five seconds left Saturday night and High Point survived a last-second 3-point attempt for a 58-57 victory over Radford. The Highlanders (12-13, 7-7 Big South) trailed at the half 38-26 and took their first lead at 57-56 with 15 seconds to go on two foul shots by Whit Holcomb-Faye. After Gathings made his free throws for the Panthers (16-10, 9-6), Holcomb-Faye missed a desperation 3-pointer at the buzzer. The Panthers began the game on a 13-0 run and led by as many as 16 before the Highlanders used 9-2 and 10-4 spurts in the second half to get back into the game. Zione White led High Point with 18 points, hitting 5-for-9 from 3-point range. Joshua Chambers had 10. Holcomb-Faye scored 19 points for the Highlanders, who were 3-for-19 from behing the arc compared to 6-for-12 for High Point. Aaron Gill and Brandon Jeffers each added 11.
